{
  "stem": "1292.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there was non-Jewish-- three brothers, I remember, Kafchinski was their name, lovely people who was very involved on the high position in this business, yes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then, when both brothers Alexandrovicz fled, the business was taken by what was called then a 'Treuhander.' And I remember his name, a German-- Kiesel was his name.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And well, the bosses wasn't there, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The business still did carry on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "treuhander was-- is a German [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] word for a person who steps in as an official to take over the business.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was many, many Jewish firm [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was disowned, and then the German [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Treuhanders ?] did step in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I continued to work there until until ghetto was formed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember-- it was a very strong impression, because we did think that the Polish was well-equipped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a young person, I did think their uniform was always spic-and-span and tidy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I did think, somehow, Poland is strong.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Jews, I must also add-- the Jews was during the [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Marshal ?] Pilsudski reign-- The Jews--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [SIGHS] I think that was-- I would like to put exactly when his reign was, but [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it's a very well-known fact that during his reign, Josef Pilsudski-- the Jews did have the best time in Krakow-- well, in Poland.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a very tolerant man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews really did, at this time, enjoy freedom and prosper.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember when he die from-- the school took part in the funeral.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was very moved by it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was a dying era for a lot of freedom for the Jews in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I think it was 1935.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
